    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>Currently a message is resent as is. This implies use of the originally assigned messageID, and works because we are by default tolerant against duplicate messageIDs .  To be strictly compliant, the resent  message should be given a new ID. Once we are updating the headers, we may also either remove any pre-existing SequenceAcknowledgement header (it  may be out-of-date, but that does not cause any harm) or, for  efficiency, replace it with an up-to-date SequenceAcknowledgement.<br/>
Requires re-running the message through a selective chain of  interceptors or else a manual approach to updating the headers in question. and subsequently re-marshalling the messge.</p>
            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

